  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "`geth` uses `elastic/sigar` to report the memory size and calculate the perfect size for the cache. `sigar`'s `mem.Get` returns 0, which cause the cache size to be 0 down the chain...\r\n\r\n```go\r\nif err := mem.Get(); err == nil {\r\n\tallowance := int(mem.Total / 1024 / 1024 / 3)\r\n\tif cache := ctx.GlobalInt(utils.CacheFlag.Name); cache > allowance {\r\n\t\tlog.Warn(\"Sanitizing cache to Go's GC limits\", \"provided\", cache, \"updated\", allowance)\r\n\t\tctx.GlobalSet(utils.CacheFlag.Name, strconv.Itoa(allowance))\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n...and cause a stack trace because a bloom filter size is 0 (note the irony of the comment)\r\n\r\n```go\r\nbloom, err := bloomfilter.New(memory*1024*1024*8, 3)\r\nif err != nil {\r\n\tpanic(fmt.Sprintf(\"failed to create bloom: %v\", err)) // Can't happen, here for sanity\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI have created a workaround PR, and this is a tracker issue while I investigate what is going wrong on the `sigar` side.\r\n\r\nNote that there is a similar issue that got closed by the bot on windows: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/3343, although `sigar` seems to have fixed its windows version since.",
